, conversion, and Shabbat. This book presents a crucial piece of scholarship in understanding the history and current dynamics of the relation between state and religion in Israel, and, in doing so, provides a unique perspective on the future potential solutions to this social rift.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aJewsxIdentity. 0aJudaism and statezIsrael. 0aReligion and statezIsrael. 7aHISTORY / Middle East / Israel & Palestine.2bisacsh  aChurch.  aIsrael constitution.  aIsrael.  aIsraeli constitutional law.  aIsraeli history.  aJudaism.  aNation-state.  aState and Religion.  aZionism.1 aRubinshṭain, Elyaḳim, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aRubinstein, Justice Elyakim, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertAcademic Studies Press Complete eBook-Package 2023z978311102354008iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG Plus PP Package 2023 Part 2z978311117804208iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2023 Englishz978311131929208iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2023z9783111318912oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE History 2023 Englishz978311131913108iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE History 2023z9783111318189oZDB-23-DEG40uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/979888719090740uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9798887190907423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9798887190907/original  a978-3-11-102354-0  Academic Studies Press Complete eBook-Package 2023b2023  a978-3-11-117804-2  DG Plus PP Package 2023 Part 2b2023  a978-3-11-131913-1  EBOOK PACKAGE History 2023 Englishb2023  a978-3-11-131929-2  EBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2023 